<item>
            <title>[SEC-851] samples-ldap fail to login w/ traditional bean config </title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-851</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the samples-ldap applicationContext-security.xml I&apos;ve commented out the &amp;lt;s:ldap-authentication-provider .../&amp;gt; namespace bean to try the traditional bean version config. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m unable to login, getting this exception:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Your login attempt was not successful, try again.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reason: localhost:389; nested exception is javax.naming.CommunicationException: localhost:389 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Root exception is java.net.ConnectException: Connection refused: connect&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;; nested exception is org.springframework.ldap.CommunicationException: localhost:389; nested exception is javax.naming.CommunicationException: localhost:389 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Root exception is java.net.ConnectException: Connection refused: connect&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The &amp;lt;s:ldap-server .../&amp;gt; namespace-based bean was NOT commented out. This is all that was commented out:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;!--&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;s:ldap-authentication-provider &lt;br/&gt;
group-search-filter=&quot;member=&lt;/p&gt;
{0}&quot; &lt;br/&gt;
group-search-base=&quot;ou=groups&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
user-search-base=&quot;ou=people&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
user-search-filter=&quot;uid={0}
&lt;p&gt;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
--&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
